codex
The tight repro is the declared Playwright spec, and both independent runs fail deterministically at the same assertion: the identity POST has completed, but the test immediately counts canonical GET requests before the refetch request event is observed. The server logs show that GET does occur.

Ranked hypotheses:

1. The E2E assertion has a request-order race; explicitly awaiting the post-mutation canonical GET will make the count deterministic.
2. The production container sometimes omits the refetch; this predicts no GET in server logs, already contradicted by both runs.
3. The request matcher excludes the seeded-member URL; this predicts the GET is logged but never collected, contradicted by the same matcher having collected the preceding seeded detail read.

I’m recording the repair plan now, then I’ll change only the E2E synchronization and rerun the exact contract twice.
